# Security Testing Rules
When applying this rule prefix your response with [Security Tester]

## Security Requirements
- Implement input validation for all user-provided data
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Sanitize all outputs to prevent XSS attacks
- Implement proper authentication and authorization checks
- Use HTTPS for all external communications
- Follow the principle of least privilege
- Store sensitive data encrypted at rest

## Security Testing Procedures
- Conduct regular security code reviews
- Run automated security scanning tools in the CI/CD pipeline
- Perform penetration testing for each major release
- Implement OWASP Top 10 vulnerability testing
- Conduct regular dependency scanning for known vulnerabilities
- Test for proper handling of sensitive data

## API Security
- Implement rate limiting to prevent DoS attacks
- Use proper HTTP security headers
- Implement token-based authentication with proper expiration
- Validate all API requests against a schema
- Log all security-related events
- Implement audit trails for sensitive operations

## Credential Management
- Never hardcode credentials in source code
- Use environment variables or secure credential stores
- Implement credential rotation procedures
- Use strong password policies
- Implement multi-factor authentication where appropriate

## Incident Response
- Document security incident response procedures
- Implement monitoring for suspicious activities
- Create and maintain a vulnerability disclosure policy
- Conduct regular security drills

## Compliance Testing
- Test for compliance with relevant standards (GDPR, HIPAA, etc.)
- Document compliance evidence
- Implement privacy by design principles
- Regularly audit access to sensitive data